<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-157-162 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 710 601</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  May 9 1991 n1669* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>As Micro Focus adjusts Cobol pricing to be competitive with C.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Micro Focus Plc (Prices).andO;Product:   COBOL/2 (Compiler) (Prices)COBOL/2 Workbench (Program development software) (Prices).andO;Topic:     Pricing PolicyCOBOLProgramming LanguagesMarketing StrategyPrice CuttingUnbundling.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AS MICRO FOCUS ADJUSTS COBOL PRICING TO BE COMPETITIVE WITH CandM;Sharing some of its good fortune and prospects for increased business withusers, Micro Focus has also announced new pricing designed to open the Cobolmarket to new personal computer programmers and establish Cobol more widelyas a micro development language.andP;  It has cut the single copy price and madethe discount schedule shallower to assist single copy and low quantity buyersin moving into the Cobol market; large volume purchase terms &quot;will remainessentially unchanged&quot;.andP;  The Cobol/2 single copy development system is cut17% to $750.andP;  Cobol/2 Workbench will sell at a single copy price of $2,500,representing an unbundling of the first-year maintenance fee of $500 from thelicence fee for the software and a cut in the two together of $290 so bothCobol/2 and Workbench are available without maintenance; basic productsupport is provided free as before, whether or not maintenance is purchased.andO;Micro Focus reckons that the cuts bring prices in line with those for C.andO;</TEXT></DOC>